http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/NAK-Media-Achievement-Awards-function/article14012613.ece

The News Papers Association of Karnataka is hosting its 4{+t}{+h}State NAK Media Achievement Awards 2015 function on Sunday (January 24) at NIMHANS Convention Centre, Hosur Road. As many as 53 achievers from visual and print media, medicine, social service, education, political and other fields will be honoured in recognition of their contribution to their respective fields. Chief Minister Siddaramaiah, Art of Living founder Sri Sri Ravishankar, Dharmadhikari of Sri Kshetra Dharmasthala Veerendra Heggade are expected to event.